The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, May 25, 2004 				 Amin calls meet on jute mill closure
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, May 24: Labour minister Mohammad Amin has convened a meeting of jute mill workers on Thursday and another with mill owners on Friday to discuss the closure of mills in quick succession.																								About nine jute mills are closed now, including the three which closed down over the last week. The representatives of the Indian Jute Mill Association will meet the negotiating council to sort out the problem, he said.																								Over 40,000 workers have been rendered jobless statewide because of the closed mills.																								Chief secretary Ashok Gupta today met representatives of the association to ascertain the reasons for the closure. 
